Ca' Furlan Prosecco
Veneto, Italy
89 points - Beverage Tasting Institute

Ca' Furlan  Prosecco is light straw in color and displays scents of fresh pear, white peach, pineapple, citrus, white flowers, and marzipan. 

This cheerful and easy-drinking sparkler offers refreshing flavors of spiced apple, white peach, and lemon verbana, along with notes of vanilla and brioche. The off-dry palate is balanced nicely by a crisp acidity and a light yeast note. The finish is clean and pleasant. 

An incredible value in sparkling wine, Ca' Furlan Prosecco  would be a delicious start your Thanksgiving meal. It's versatile and dynamic, bubbly and softly sweet, perfect alongside hors d'oeuvres as well as  turkey, stuffing, and mashed potatoes.

Josh Cellars Cabernet Sauvignon 
North Coast, California
90 Points - Wine Enthusiast
   
Josh Cellars is a blend of 100% Cabernet Sauvignon grapes, sourced from organically grown and sustainably farmed vineyards in the Red Hills of Lake County, California. You will find an attractive bouquet of ripe black currant, and deep, dark fruits, accented by smoke and spice. 
 
In the mouth, layers of silky red and black currant, are complemented by spicy berry notes, as well as red licorice, pomegranate, ripe plum, and gentle nuances of vanilla, cocoa, and smoky oak. This incredible California Cabernet is big, bold, smooth, and supple all at once. The tannins are soft and the satiny mouthfeel carries through the long, expressive finish. 

Josh Cellars Cabernet is very approachable, and drinks well on its own, but also pairs wonderfully with foods such as grilled steak, prime rib, roast chicken, veal parmigiana, and pasta marinara.
 
Regular Price: $18.99
Special Price: $14.99

Woodford Distiller's Select Bourbon 
Versailles, Kentucky 
2014, 2012, 2011 SF World Spirits Competition, Gold Medal 
2013 SF World Spirits Competition: Double Gold Medal 
2012 Int'l Spirits Challenge: Best in Class, Gold Medal 
95 Points - Wine Enthusiast Magazine 
91 Points, Exceptional - Beverage Tasting Institute

"Interesting aromas of freshly waxed wood, saddle soap, suede, tapioca and pecan nougat with a round, supple, dry-yet-fruity medium-full body and a long, dried fruit, roasted nut, grainy pastry dough, mint leaf, cola, sassafras, peppery spice, and mineral ore accented finish. Very distinctive, intricate, and stylish." - Beverage Tasting Institute, 91 Points  

Appearance: Clean, brilliant honey amber.

Nose: Heavy with rich dried fruit, hints of mint and oranges covered with a dusting of cocoa. Faint vanilla and tobacco spice. 

Taste: Rich, chewy, rounded and smooth, with complex citrus, cinnamon and cocoa. Toffee, caramel, chocolate and spice notes abound. 

Finish: Silky smooth, almost creamy at first, with a long, warm, satisfying tail.

Cigar City Brewing Co. Mixed Pack
Tampa, FL

Jai Alai
An intense bouquet of tangerine and candied orange peel entice the nose while flavors of clementines, Valencia orange and subtle caramel provide counterpoint to an assertive bitterness and rich malt character. Bold hop flavor and aroma from six different hop varietals is front and center in this flavorful American IPA.
 
Florida Cracker
Citrus aromas of oranges and lime leaves mingle with bubblegum and dried flowers on the nose of this hazy and refreshing Belgian-style White Ale. High carbonation and herbaceous bitterness quench the thirst while lemon-lime esters and flavors of Valencia orange add unique depth of flavor and complexity.
 
Guayabera
Bright berry, lime leaf and tangerine aromas and flavors imparted by our exclusive use of Citra hops are deftly balanced by an assertive bitterness and moderate breadiness from a simple malt bill. Infinitely quaffable but worthy of careful consideration.
 
Florida Man
A modern Double IPA with a tropical expression from the blend of American hops including Pacific Jade, Galaxy, Azacca, Lemon Drop and Simcoe is balanced by delicate peach esters from a unique Double IPA yeast and a dash of Canadian honey malt.
